      "writtenOn": "2020-07-08T08:49:00Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I still don\u0027t have a good picture of how parameters for fixtures works.\n\nParameterized tests are useful because test functions have to be a simple top-level function with a fixed signature (func(ctx context.Context, s *testing.State)). But the situation is different for fixtures. I imagine we can parameterize fixtures in the following way for example:\n\n func newChromeFixture(opts ...Option) testing.Fixture { ... }\n\n func init() {\n   testing.AddFixt(\u0026testing.Fixt{\n     Name: \"fake_logged_in\",\n     Impl: newChromeFixture(),\n     ...\n   })\n   testing.AddFixt(\u0026testing.Fixt{\n     Name: \"gaia_logged_in\",\n     Impl: newChromeFixture(GAIALogin(\"user\", \"pass\")),\n     ...\n   })\n }\n\nPros about this approach is that parameterized fixtures don\u0027t share the same impl, so it\u0027s safer.\n\nDo you want to support Fixt.Params from the beginning? Then I think we need more discussion in the design doc.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 20,
        "startChar": 3,
        "endLine": 20,
        "endChar": 15
      },
      "revId": "66a492eccc8346138e8ab4421eaa224ef0c20b48",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
