      "writtenOn": "2020-07-08T08:49:00Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "With this sequence, Tast might enter an infinite loop. For example, let\u0027s say we have two fixtures A and B, and B.Adjust always fails. Then a possible sequence would be:\n\n- A.Prepare\n- B.Prepare\n- A.Adjust\n- B.Adjust -\u003e fail\n- B.Close\n- B.Prepare\n- B.Adjust -\u003e fail\n- B.Close\n- B.Prepare\n- B.Adjust -\u003e fail\n- ...\n\nDo you have any idea to avoid such loops?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 162,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 162,
        "endChar": 55
      },
